 BILLY Connolly said a tearful goodbye at the funeral of his sister yesterday. 
The comedian attended the service of Florence Dickson with wife Pamela Stephenson at Christ the King Church on Glasgow's south side.
The 72-year-old, who revealed he is suffering from Parkinson's disease last year, carried his sibling's coffin and greeted mourners outside afterwards.
Florence died last week, aged 74.
Billy has previously described how the pair were raised by two aunts after being abandoned by their mother.
